><strong>Rental subsidy<\\\/strong><br \/>Proposed to pay 1 month\\u2019s rent for lower income tenants living in public rental units.<\\\/li>\\n    \n\n<li><strong>Examination fees waiver<\\\/strong><br \/>Proposed to waive examination fees for candidates sitting 2021 HKDSE Examination.<\\\/li>\\n    \n\n<li><strong>Rental reduction or provide rental subsidy<\\\/strong><br \/>Proposed to provide $100 million rental subsidy to local recycling enterprises for 6 months. Proposed to reduce 50% of the rental for Government properties or hire charges for civic centres under Leisure and Cultural Services Department for 6 months. Waive the fees and rent for cruise lines and cruise terminal tenants for 6 months.<\\\/li>\\n<\\\/ol>\\n\\n\n\n<p>For detailed information of the Hong Kong Budget 2020\\\/21, please visit: <a href=\\\"https:\\\/\\\/www.budget.gov.hk\\\/2020\\\/eng\\\/speech.html\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">https:\\\/\\\/www.budget.gov.hk\\\/2020\\\/eng\\\/speech.html<\\\/a><\\\/p>\"}}]}]}]}],\"version\":\"1.22.8\",\"props\":[]} --><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>On 26 February, the Financial Secretary, Paul Chan Mo-po, unveiled the following major measures in the 2020\/21 Hong Kong Budget&#8230;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":1996,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[276],"tags":[],"acf":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.acclime.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1622"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.acclime.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.acclime.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.acclime.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.acclime.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=1622"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.acclime.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1622\/revisions"}]